cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a novel framework for imitation learning that relies on exploration and distillation of experience into a policy. This falls under the domain of machine learning.
- cs.RO (Robotics): The paper evaluates the proposed framework in two real-world settings involving robots (Baxter and TurtleBot) performing tasks. This falls under the domain of robotics.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper uses sequences of images to demonstrate the desired task and to train the policy. This falls under the domain of computer vision.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a new paradigm for imitation learning that reduces the reliance on expert supervision. This falls under the domain of artificial intelligence.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes a policy that can be used to control the behavior of a robot in performing a task. This falls under the domain of systems and control.
